Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper proposes a novel text encryption method and emphasizes on information security. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed method is based on deep learning and involves training a deep learning model to establish a word vector table. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a method that involves using hyperparameters in deep learning models to generate a secret key for encryption. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed method and its lower demand for key redistribution. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves the transformation of plaintext to ciphertext and discusses the security and efficiency of the proposed method.
